What do you do
when you think

13:42.788 --> 13:44.488
You're doing what's right,
but you're really just confused

13:44.491 --> 13:46.024
And you feel like
life is trying

13:46.026 --> 13:47.992
To throw you
on the ground?

13:47.994 --> 13:49.527
You hang on, riley.

13:53.967 --> 13:56.100
I'm a little tired.

13:56.102 --> 13:58.169
Please don't go anywhere.

13:58.171 --> 13:59.904
I won't.

14:01.208 --> 14:03.374
I'm gonna be here
a long time.

14:04.878 --> 14:06.110
Okay.

14:21.161 --> 14:22.727
(grunts)

14:22.729 --> 14:24.028
Honey?

14:24.030 --> 14:25.563
Sweetie?

14:25.565 --> 14:29.200
Um, I love you
and I love your teen angst,

14:29.202 --> 14:31.603
But I have to go to work
so that I can afford you.

14:32.672 --> 14:34.572
Oh, thank goodness.

14:34.574 --> 14:36.307
(grunts)

14:36.309 --> 14:38.543
Okay, she's all yours.

14:38.545 --> 14:40.144
She drools a little.

14:44.184 --> 14:46.150
Go to school.
Brush your teeth.

14:46.152 --> 14:48.052
-Comb your hair.
-Mmm.

14:48.054 --> 14:50.889
-You're not my mother.
-No, it's me.

14:52.425 --> 14:54.192
(both laugh nervously)

14:54.194 --> 14:55.927
How did you time
with lucas go?

14:55.929 --> 14:59.898
It-- we sat there
with absolutely
nothing to say.

14:59.900 --> 15:02.233
-Been there, done that.
-Yeah, well...

15:02.235 --> 15:03.868
You guys won't have to worry
about that anymore

15:03.870 --> 15:05.603
-Now that you're brother
and sister, you know.
-Mm-hmm.

15:05.605 --> 15:07.505
You guys have loads
to-- to talk about.

15:07.507 --> 15:08.740
I love talking to him.

15:08.742 --> 15:10.441
I love making fun of him.

15:10.443 --> 15:11.576
Why?

15:11.578 --> 15:13.745
-Why do I love
to make fun of him?
-Yeah.

15:13.747 --> 15:16.114
Because he's great.

15:16.116 --> 15:17.248
Yeah.

15:17.250 --> 15:21.386
And he needs someone
like me to take him down.

15:21.388 --> 15:24.188
-And he needs
someone like you--
-for why?

15:24.190 --> 15:25.690
For why
does he need me?

15:27.093 --> 15:28.393
To build him up,

15:28.395 --> 15:30.261
To tell his
ranger rick stories to,

15:30.263 --> 15:33.598
-And make him feel like a hero.
-(both laugh)

15:33.600 --> 15:37.101
You like his stories
and-- and he likes yours.

15:39.606 --> 15:40.805
Yeah.

15:51.618 --> 15:53.418
-Hi, riley.
-Hi, charlie.

15:53.420 --> 15:55.920
-Riley, I can't be
your brother anymore.
-Hey, friar.

15:55.922 --> 15:58.122
Do you think you can
pick a better time
for this big announcement?

15:58.124 --> 15:59.390
Riley and I are
gonna go on a date.

15:59.392 --> 16:00.491
You are?

16:01.561 --> 16:02.627
No holding hands
or talking.

16:02.629 --> 16:03.995
Best date ever.

16:03.997 --> 16:05.964
I know it's not,
but it's what I got.

16:05.966 --> 16:08.066
Those are the rules?

16:08.068 --> 16:10.501
Who goes on a date
and doesn't talk
to each other?

16:14.407 --> 16:15.673
Oh, yeah. We do.

16:15.675 --> 16:16.975
Hi.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.042
Hello.

16:19.346 --> 16:21.279
Hey riley,
can we go?

16:21.281 --> 16:22.347
I like to be there

16:22.349 --> 16:23.614
For the previews
of coming attractions.

16:23.616 --> 16:25.183
When I'm not there
for the previews

16:25.185 --> 16:27.518
Of coming attractions,
I feel like I didn't
see the whole movie.

16:27.520 --> 16:28.753
Hey riley,
what do you do

16:28.755 --> 16:29.921
When you sit
next to huckleberry?

16:29.923 --> 16:31.856
Maya, I can't give
you advice like that.

16:31.858 --> 16:33.858
Sure you can.
You're his sister, right?

16:33.860 --> 16:35.326
Nope. Not anymore.

16:35.328 --> 16:37.195
-Why?
-Auggie says we can't.

16:37.197 --> 16:38.663
-Hey, friar--
-and you know what?

16:38.665 --> 16:40.431
I think he's right.
You already have
a great brother.

16:40.433 --> 16:42.300
Hey, friar!

16:42.302 --> 16:43.935
Then what will you be?

16:43.937 --> 16:46.404
He'll be me,
because it's me now.

16:48.108 --> 16:50.975
Yeah. Sorry.
You have every right.

16:50.977 --> 16:54.178
I also want to be there
early to get snacks

16:54.180 --> 16:56.447
'cause if we're not talking
or holding hands,

16:56.449 --> 16:58.883
I was gonna buy
some popcorn and licorice.

16:58.885 --> 17:00.318
You mean popcorn
and chocolate.

17:00.320 --> 17:02.286
-I'm not you!
-Okay!

17:02.288 --> 17:04.322
Anyway, auggie loves you, riley.

17:04.324 --> 17:06.391
So, I'm gonna step back
from being your brother.

17:06.393 --> 17:08.192
-Say "me now."
-me now.

17:08.194 --> 17:09.694
You have every right.

17:11.164 --> 17:13.064
I break the licorice
into little pieces

17:13.066 --> 17:14.866
So every time I take
a handful of popcorn,

17:14.868 --> 17:16.100
I get a surprise.

17:17.670 --> 17:19.337
I'm adorable.

17:19.339 --> 17:20.738
How are you not seeing this?

17:20.740 --> 17:22.240
Zay:
You see?

17:22.242 --> 17:24.375
Lucas does anything
for anybody.

17:24.377 --> 17:26.010
I mean, he sacrifices
being riley's brother

17:26.012 --> 17:27.211
So he doesn't
hurt auggie's feelings.

17:27.213 --> 17:28.846
Well, same with riley.
She's stepping back

17:28.848 --> 17:30.681
From lucas because she's
doing exactly the same thing.

17:30.683 --> 17:34.218
-Farkle, stop.
-But I thought she didn't
like him like that anymore.

17:34.220 --> 17:36.621
No, riley's stepping back
from lucas because she doesn't--

17:38.425 --> 17:40.992
Okay, she ends up
with farkle.

17:40.994 --> 17:42.260
How did we not see
that coming?

17:43.563 --> 17:45.897
Farkle, you don't know
what's going on.

17:45.899 --> 17:48.032
-Stop thinking.
-I know auggie's right.

17:48.034 --> 17:49.200
He's your only brother.

17:49.202 --> 17:50.535
I've seen the way
you look at auggie,

17:50.537 --> 17:52.036
And I've seen the way
you look at lucas.

17:52.038 --> 17:53.337
It's not the same.

17:53.339 --> 17:55.373
I-- I think I know
my own feelings.

17:55.375 --> 17:56.941
-You're a liar.
-Farkle.

17:56.943 --> 17:58.109
You're lying to yourself.

17:58.111 --> 18:00.244
Lucas and I don't
make a good couple.

18:04.017 --> 18:05.383
Thank you very much, lucas.

18:05.385 --> 18:07.318
I had a wonderful time.

18:08.688 --> 18:10.254
You're welcome, riley.
I also had

18:10.256 --> 18:11.789
A wonderful time as well.

18:14.127 --> 18:17.295
You were both just nervous
because that's not who you are.

18:17.297 --> 18:19.397
I guess the thing
I miss most about texas

18:19.399 --> 18:20.798
Are the pets
that I used to have.

18:20.800 --> 18:23.367
I had a hamster.

18:23.369 --> 18:25.103
I had 24 horses.

18:25.105 --> 18:26.504
You win.

18:28.408 --> 18:30.475
Tell me about them.

18:30.477 --> 18:32.043
Okay, okay.

18:32.045 --> 18:33.611
But what about maya?

18:35.448 --> 18:36.280
Huh-hurr.

18:36.282 --> 18:38.449
Har-har!

18:38.451 --> 18:42.620
Huh-hurr!

18:45.458 --> 18:48.426
I'm not really sure
how maya feels.

18:48.428 --> 18:49.794
You're not sure?

18:49.796 --> 18:51.829
How can you not be sure?

18:51.831 --> 18:53.431
This isn't about her.

18:53.433 --> 18:55.366
I'm talking
about how you feel.

19:02.108 --> 19:03.941
Farkle, how do you
even know about that?

19:03.943 --> 19:06.010
-You weren't even there.
-Doesn't matter.

19:06.012 --> 19:08.412
What you're thinking
is how you really feel.

19:09.616 --> 19:11.516
I don't care.

19:11.518 --> 19:13.918
Farkle, maya is my best friend.

19:13.920 --> 19:16.420
She cares about him
and he cares about her too.

19:22.462 --> 19:24.095
You questioning
my leadership, hop-along?

19:24.097 --> 19:25.930
Okay, these names
you're calling me are

19:25.932 --> 19:27.165
Killing my street cred.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.534
You actually put thought
into our little game, don't you?

19:29.536 --> 19:31.536
I actually do.

19:31.538 --> 19:33.371
(shudders)

19:33.373 --> 19:35.373
Oh, no.

19:38.611 --> 19:40.945
Hello.

19:40.947 --> 19:43.381
I'm bucky mcboing boing.

19:44.350 --> 19:46.117
I want maya to be happy.

19:47.654 --> 19:49.720
Hey, maya, it looks like
lucas here's gettin' all

19:49.722 --> 19:51.355
Fired up on your behalf.

19:52.492 --> 19:53.558
Thank you, lucas.

19:53.560 --> 19:54.692
But it's just an art class.

19:54.694 --> 19:55.993
I feel bad.

19:55.995 --> 19:57.628
They're taking away
something you're very good at.

19:57.630 --> 20:00.364
-You've never said
that to me before.
-I have said it.

20:00.366 --> 20:02.567
Yeah, but not, like,
right to my face
when you were looking at me.

20:02.569 --> 20:05.303
-I can't remember you actually--
-you're a great artist, maya.

20:07.674 --> 20:10.241
He might,
but we know he likes you.

20:12.345 --> 20:13.811
What's the matter?

20:21.754 --> 20:23.187
Hi.

20:23.189 --> 20:25.256
Even though
this just happened,

20:25.258 --> 20:28.326
There are some moments
you know you're gonna
remember forever.

20:28.328 --> 20:29.794
This is one of 'em.

20:31.931 --> 20:33.497
(sniffs)

20:40.406 --> 20:41.539
You were the first

20:41.541 --> 20:42.873
Boy I ever liked.

20:42.875 --> 20:44.909
That's big deal for me.
Are you worth it?

20:44.911 --> 20:46.444
Tell me,
and I'll believe you.

20:46.446 --> 20:48.946
I want to believe you.
Are you worth it?

20:48.948 --> 20:50.248
Yes.

20:50.250 --> 20:52.183
(screams)

20:55.221 --> 20:56.454
Hi.

20:56.456 --> 20:59.523
We were just
talking about you.

21:02.462 --> 21:04.729
Hi, I'm riley.

21:04.731 --> 21:06.597
We were just
talking about you.

21:06.599 --> 21:08.766
(chuckles)
I'm lucas.

21:08.768 --> 21:10.134
I love it.

21:14.040 --> 21:15.539
You can't tell anybody.

21:26.386 --> 21:28.452
-I will, unless you do.
-Why?

21:28.454 --> 21:30.054
Because we are growing up.

21:30.056 --> 21:31.555
And I don't know
how to handle

21:31.557 --> 21:33.124
These feelings
we're feeling.

21:33.126 --> 21:34.692
But I do know that
we don't lie to each other.

21:35.795 --> 21:37.628
We don't lie
to each other, riley.

21:38.965 --> 21:40.298
You're right.

21:42.468 --> 21:45.636
This is really hard
and maybe I just
need some time.

21:47.407 --> 21:48.572
I'm always here for you.

21:51.511 --> 21:53.210
I love you, farkle.

21:54.580 --> 21:55.913
And I love you.

21:57.517 --> 21:58.649
Now go on your date.

22:02.021 --> 22:03.554
Ready?

22:05.658 --> 22:07.491
For the previews
of coming attractions?

22:07.493 --> 22:08.693
Yeah.

22:08.695 --> 22:10.761
I'm sure we're all wondering
what happens now.

22:31.117 --> 22:32.616
How was your date?

22:33.653 --> 22:34.885
I don't know.

22:36.055 --> 22:37.254
How was your date?

22:38.324 --> 22:39.557
I don't know.

22:46.566 --> 22:48.532
Do we know anything?

22:54.374 --> 22:55.740
Ring power.

22:58.678 --> 22:59.710
Ring power.

23:01.314 --> 23:02.913
-Thunder.
-Lightning.

23:04.150 --> 23:05.750
A little scared.

23:05.752 --> 23:07.084
Me too.
